- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Use Shadcn UI components as base, customize as needed

## Styling Guidelines

### Tailwind CSS Best Practices

- Use utility classes first
- Extract repeated patterns to components
- Use CSS variables for theme colors (defined in `styles.css`)
- Follow mobile-first approach (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints)

### Color System

- Primary: `#1E4C7A` (Navy Blue - defined in CSS variables)
- Use CSS custom properties from `styles.css` for theming
- Support dark mode (use `dark:` variant when needed)

### Shadcn Components

- Install new components: `bun dlx shadcn@latest add [component]`
- Customize components by editing files in `src/components/ui/`
- Maintain consistency with existing component patterns

## Internationalization (i18n)

### Using Paraglide

- Import messages: `import * as m from '@/paraglide/messages'`
- Use `m.example_message()` for translations
- Access locale: `import { getLocale } from '@/paraglide/runtime'`
- URLs are automatically localized via router rewrite

### Translation Files

- Located in `messages/` directory (ID, EN, ZH)
- Managed via Inlang project configuration
- Use `machine-translate` script if needed: `bun machine-translate`

### Best Practices

- Always provide translations for all user-facing text
- Use semantic message keys (not generic like "text1")
- Test all language variants
- Ensure proper RTL support if needed

## Code Quality

### Linting & Formatting

- Use Biome for linting and formatting
- Run `bun check` before committing
- Follow existing code style patterns

### TypeScript

- Enable strict mode
